subsection.def:
Director
                    (署長) means the Director of Social
                Welfare;

inspector
                    (視察主任) means a person appointed under
                    section 12 to be an inspector of child care centres;

premises
                    (處所) includes any building, enclosure, ground
                or open air space;

subparagraph.content:
all the children who are under the age of 3 years habitually received
                        at the school are pupils receiving a nursery education within the meaning of
                            section 3(1) of the Education Ordinance (Cap. 279) from the school;

paragraph.content:
that for reasons connected with the situation, construction, accommodation,
                    staffing or equipment, the premises to be used for the proposed mutual help
                    child care centre are not fit to be used for that purpose;

on any ground specified in section 11B(4) which would have entitled
                him to refuse an application for exemption in respect of the mutual help child care
                centre concerned;

subparagraph.content:
in Hong Kong or elsewhere of any of the offences set out in
                            paragraph 1 or 2 of the Schedule;
                        or

paragraph.content:
the Director has received documents forwarded to him under subsection (1)
                    concerning the death of a child while in the care of a person acting as a
                    childminder;

the keeping, in respect of such centres, of registers, records,
                    time-tables,
                    menus and books of account;
